flowchart TD
    A[User navigates to /register]
    B[Registration Form is rendered]
    C[User enters Username, Email, Password, Confirm Password]
    D[Client-side validation occurs]
    E[User clicks 'Register' button]
    F[POST request sent to /api/register]
    G{Backend response}
    H[Success: New user created]
    I[Failure: Error returned]
    J[Display success message with link to login]
    K[Display error message with field highlights]

    A --> B
    B --> C
    C --> D
    D -- Valid --> E
    D -- Invalid --> K
    E --> F
    F --> G
    G -- Success --> H
    G -- Failure --> I
    H --> J
    I --> K

sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant BE as Backend

    U->>FE: Navigate to /register
    FE->>U: Render registration form
    U->>FE: Enter registration details (Username, Email, Password, Confirm Password)
    FE->>FE: Perform client-side validation (show/hide password, disable auto-fill)
    U->>FE: Click Register button
    FE->>BE: Send POST /api/register with form data
    BE-->>FE: Return success response or error details
    alt Registration Success
      FE->>U: Display "User registered successfully!" and show link to login page
    else Registration Failure
      FE->>U: Display error message (e.g., missing fields, duplicate account)
    end
